- Add `out: ./migrations` to drizzle.config.ts
- Add `generate` and `migrate` scripts to lib/db/package.json
- Generate initial migration 0000_useful_tarot.sql (all 15 tables)
- docker-compose migrate service runs `drizzle-kit migrate` instead of `push --accept-data-loss`
- Add deploy/baseline.sh: idempotent one-time script for existing push-based databases — creates drizzle.__drizzle_migrations and marks migration 0000 as applied with correct SHA-256 hash + folderMillis from journal
- update.sh: starts postgres, detects push-based DBs (tables exist but no tracking table), fails fast with clear instructions before running migrations, then applies pending migrations before container rebuild
- README: documents migration workflow, schema change process, and upgrade path from push to migrate

